cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

This paper is about lifelong learning in artificial learning systems, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves computing the importance of parameters in a neural network, which is a common technique in neural network optimization (cs.NE). The method is unsupervised, meaning it does not require labeled data, which is a characteristic of many unsupervised learning algorithms (cs.AI). The paper also includes experiments on object recognition and learning embeddings, which are tasks commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), respectively.
